notes: This version of the Kansas Road Centerline File (0801) represents the first effort to create a statewide roads layer from best available data sources. KGS integrated linework from 19 counties into the KDOT All Roads layer and created a new attribute schema for the merged dataset. Attributes were standardized to the US Postal Service Addressing Standard (Pub 28, July 2006) where possible. Address attributes are complete as per the source data but other ancillary attributes, such as road functional class and road surface, are not yet standardized or populated (see Attribute Information for details). The following county datasets have been incorporated into KRCF0801: Allen, Anderson, Barton, Bourbon, Brown, Crawford, Douglas, Gove, Edwards, Jackson, Logan, Pawnee, Riley, Scott, Sedgwick, Stafford, Thomas, Wabaunsee, Wilson.
